This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating images from text descriptions. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel attentional generative network, which could fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of a multimodal similarity model suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image-text matching, which could also place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
